subSection.paragraph:
Genomic DNA extraction, amplification of the 16S rRNA and COI genes, and sequencing followed Komai & Matsuzaki (2022) . The obtained raw DNA sequences were assembled and edited by GENETYX-MAC v. 17 (Genetyx, Tokyo , Japan ). The newly generated sequences were subjected to BLAST (Basic Local Alignment Search Tool, National Center for Biotechnology Information, NCBI) search against GenBank to check for potential contamination and find similar sequences in the database. The 16S rRNA and COI gene sequences from congeners in the GenBank were referred for DNA analyses (cf.
Kou et al . 2020
), as summarised in Table 1 . Target sequences were aligned by MUSTLE ( Edgar 2004 ) implemented in MEGA 11 (
Tamura et al . 2021
). Pairwise distances based on the Kimura 2-parameter model (K2P divergence) were calculated by MEGA 11 to compare the divergences amongst the nominated species for evaluating the validity of the taxa under consideration.

